<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1251005>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. A. Trichomycterus striatus, holotype, FMNH 7579, 71.5 mm SL, Panama, dorsal, lateral, ventral, and X-ray lateral views. B. Trichomycterus septentrionale, holotype, FMNH 59522, 88.4 mm SL, Panama, dorsal, lateral, ventral, and X-ray lateral views. Scale bar = 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1251005/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1251011>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Trichomycterus striatus, neurocranium; A. C&S specimen, UCR 0434-04, Panama, dorsal view; B. C&S specimen, UCR 0434-04, Panama, ventral view. Abreviations: Afo. Anterior fontanel; Au. Autopalatine; Be. Basi-exoccipital; De. Dentary; Epo. Epioccipital; Fr. Frontal; La. Lachrymal-antorbital; Le. Lateral ethmoid; Hy. Hyomandibula; Me. Mesethmoid; Mto. Metapterygoid; Mx. Maxilla; Pfo. Posterior fontanel; Pmx. Premaxilla; Ps. Parasphenoid; Psoc. Parietosupraoccipital; Pt. Pterotic; Qu. Quadrate; Sob. Sesamoid supraorbital; Vo. Vomer; SPP. Sphenotic-prootic-pterosphenoid complex bone; We. Weberian capsule. Scale bar = 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1251011/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1251013>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Trichomycterus cf. striatus and T. striatus, opercle (OP) and interopercle (IO); A. Draft modified from Ardila- Rodríguez (2007), CAR 36 (T. cf. striatus), Colombia, lateral view, illustration by Julio Ardila; B. C&S specimen, UCR 0434- 04 (T. striatus), Panama, lateral view. Scale bar = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1251013/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1251015>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Trichomycterus striatus, (A) hyoid arch, (B) pectoral girdle, and (C) pelvic girdle; C&S specimen, UCR 0434-04, Panama, ventral views. Abreviations: Ac. Anterior ceratohyal; Ba. Basipterygium; BR. Branchiostegal ray; Cl. Cleithrum; Pc. Posterior ceratohyal; Pr. Pectoral radial; Pu. Parurohyal; Sc. Scapulocoracoid; Vh. ventral hypohyal. Scale bar = 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1251015/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1251017>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Trichomycterus cf. striatus and T. striatus, opercle, branchial archs; A. Draft modified from Ardila-Rodríguez (2007), CAR 36 (T. cf. striatus), Colombia, dorsal view, illustration by Julio Ardila; B. C&S specimen, UCR 0434-04 (T. striatus), Panama, dorsal view. C. C&S specimen, UCR 0434-04, Panama, ventral view. Abreviations: BB. Basibranchial; CB. Ceratobranchial; EB. Epibranchial; HB. Hypobranchial; PB. Pharyngobranchial; UDP. Upper dentigerous plate. Scale bar = 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1251017/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1251019>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Trichomycterus striatus, caudal skeleton; A. C&S specimen, UCR 0111-18, Costa Rica, lateral view; B. C&S specimen, UCR 0434-04, Panama, lateral view. Abreviations: CCC. Compound caudal centrum (preural centrum 1 + ural centrum 1); CFE. Caudal-fin elements (principal caudal-fin rays); DPR. Dorsal procurrent rays; H. Hypural; HS. Hemal spine; NS. Neural spine; Ph. Parhypural; U. Uroneural; VPR. Ventral procurrent rays. Scale bar = 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1251019/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1251007>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Trichomycterus striatus, intraspecific variation in body color pattern; A. UCR 0111-18, 29.4 mm SL, Costa Rica, lateral view; B. UCR 0434-04, 35.9 mm SL, Panama, lateral view; C. UCR 0434-04, 42.7 mm SL, Panama, lateral view; D. UCR 0434-04, 52.1 mm SL, Panama, lateral view; E. UCR 0111-18, 69.2 mm SL, Costa Rica, lateral view; F. UCR 0434-04, 75.4 mm SL, Panama, lateral view; G. UCR 0434-04, 77.6 mm SL, Panama, lateral view; H. UCR 0434-04, 119.9 mm SL, Panama, lateral view. Scale bar = 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1251007/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1251009>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Trichomycterus striatus, fresh specimens; A. DZSJRP 21188, 113.0 mm SL, Costa Rica, dorsal, lateral, and ventral views; B. DZSJRP 21188, 57.7 mm SL, Costa Rica, dorsal, lateral, and ventral views; C. Live specimen (not preserved), lateral view, 78.9 mm SL, captured at the Limón River, 08°49’27.0”N 83°01’38.6”W, Puntarenas, Costa Rica, on 2 Oct 2007 by Jorge Picado; photograph by Jorge Picado. Scale bar = 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1251009/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1251021>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Map of lower Central America (Costa Rica and Panama) showing the geographic distribution of Trichomycterus striatus. Plus symbol indicates the type locality, triangle represent new locality record (DZSJRP 21188)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1251021/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

